2 Day 2

2.1 Number of blades cleared

2.1.1 Graph

ggplot(num2, aes(x = Length, y = Numbercleared, color = Hardness, group = Hardness)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 0.25, width = 0.05) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = mean, geom = "point", size = 4) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = mean, geom = "line") +
  ylab("Number of blades cleared") +
  scale_color_brewer("Hardness", palette = "Dark2") + 
  theme_minimal(base_size = 18) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

2.1.2 Model selection

Note: a first pass at the model showed that the residuals werent very clean. I used a square root transformation to correct some of it.

m_full_num_2 <- lmer(sqrt(Numbercleared) ~ Length * Hardness + (1 | ColonyID), data = num2, REML = FALSE)
m_no_interaction_num_2 <- lmer(sqrt(Numbercleared) ~ Length + Hardness + (1 | ColonyID), data = num2, REML = FALSE)
anova(m_full_num_2, m_no_interaction_num_2)
## Data: num2
## Models:
## m_no_interaction_num_2: sqrt(Numbercleared) ~ Length + Hardness + (1 | ColonyID)
## m_full_num_2: sqrt(Numbercleared) ~ Length * Hardness + (1 | ColonyID)
##                        Df    AIC    BIC  logLik deviance  Chisq Chi Df
## m_no_interaction_num_2  5 437.82 449.73 -213.91   427.82              
## m_full_num_2            6 435.38 449.67 -211.69   423.38 4.4458      1
##                        Pr(>Chisq)  
## m_no_interaction_num_2             
## m_full_num_2              0.03499 *
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

There is a statistical difference between the full model and the model without interaction.Well continue with the full model.

2.1.3 Model diagnostic

diagnostic <- augment(m_full_num_2)

a <- ggplot(diagnostic, aes(x = .fitted, y = .wtres)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 18) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

b <- ggplot(diagnostic, aes(x = .fitted, y = sqrt(abs(.wtres)))) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 18) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

y <- quantile(diagnostic$.resid, c(0.25, 0.75))
x <- qnorm(c(0.25, 0.75))
slope <- diff(y) / diff(x)
int   <- y[1] - slope * x[1]     
c <- ggplot(fortify(m_full_num_2), aes(sample = .resid)) +
  geom_qq() +
  geom_abline(intercept = int, slope = slope) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 18) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

cowplot::plot_grid(a, b, c)

Not perfect, but thatll do.

2.1.4 Model evaluation

sjp.lmer(m_full_num_2, type = "fe", prnt.plot = FALSE)$plot +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 18) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

2.2.2 Model selection

Note: a first pass at the model showed that the residuals werent very clean. I used a square root transformation to correct some of it.

m_full_prop_2 <- lmer(sqrt(Propcleared) ~ Length * Hardness + (1 | ColonyID), data = prop2, REML = FALSE)
m_no_interaction_prop_2 <- lmer(sqrt(Propcleared) ~ Length + Hardness + (1 | ColonyID), data = prop2, REML = FALSE)
anova(m_full_prop_2, m_no_interaction_prop_2)
## Data: prop2
## Models:
## m_no_interaction_prop_2: sqrt(Propcleared) ~ Length + Hardness + (1 | ColonyID)
## m_full_prop_2: sqrt(Propcleared) ~ Length * Hardness + (1 | ColonyID)
##                         Df    AIC    BIC  logLik deviance Chisq Chi Df
## m_no_interaction_prop_2  5 14.614 26.525 -2.3072   4.6145             
## m_full_prop_2            6 16.614 30.906 -2.3070   4.6140 5e-04      1
##                         Pr(>Chisq)
## m_no_interaction_prop_2           
## m_full_prop_2               0.9824

No statistical difference between the full model and the model without interaction. Well continue with the model without interaction.
